content: Is there any up-to-date documentation on the various kernels available in JupyterHub (i.e., the choices shown when you start a new Launcher)? For example, I have been using CMIP6 2019.10a over 2019.10, based on someone's recommendation quite awhile ago, but I'm not sure what the difference is, and maybe something else would be better for my purposes. Thanks!
@Louisa Emmons, you may find this page to be useful: https://arc.ucar.edu/knowledge_base/70549913...
